com.ibm.team.repository.common

Interface IBaselineComparison


  • public interface IBaselineComparison
    Expresses the differences and similarities between two auditable baselines. These two baselines are identified as the "prior" baseline and the "after" baseline, although no particular time ordering is assumed.
    Since:
    0.5

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.util.List getAddedItems()
      Get the items added to the after baseline that were absent in the prior baseline.
      java.util.List getChangedItems()
      Get the items that are present in different states in both baselines.
      java.util.List getIdenticalItems()
      Get the items that are present in the same state in both baselines.
      java.util.List getRemovedItems()
      Get the items removed from the after baseline that were present in the prior baseline.

        java.util.List getAddedItems()
        Get the items added to the after baseline that were absent in the prior baseline.

      • getRemovedItems

        java.util.List getRemovedItems()
        Get the items removed from the after baseline that were present in the prior baseline.
        Returns:

      • getIdenticalItems

        java.util.List getIdenticalItems()
        Get the items that are present in the same state in both baselines.
        Returns:
        List (element type: IAuditableHandle s.t. IItemHandle.hasStateId() is true) of identical item states; no duplicates; no particular order; never null

      • getChangedItems

        java.util.List getChangedItems()

        Returns:
